{"id":25748,"title":"[Modern tactics antihypertensive therapy: a place of Angiotensin converting enzyme inhibitors].","abstract":"In a review article we presents an analysis of the new recommendations of the European Society of hypertension (ESH) and the European Society of Cardiology (ESC) on the management of arterial hypertension (2013). Main attention is paid to the tactics of antihypertensive therapy and the choice of drugs in the treatment of early hypertension. Target blood pressure levels in are discussed the historical aspect. Criteria for applicftion of monotherapy in the treatment patients with hypertension, and possible mechanisms for selection of antihypertensive drug are also discussed. ","date":"2014-09-02","categories":"Cardiovascular Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25177790","annotations":[{"name":"Antihypertensive drug","weight":0.849915,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antihypertensive_drug"},{"name":"Hypertension","weight":0.824766,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hypertension"},{"name":"ACE inhibitor","weight":0.800429,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ACE_inhibitor"},{"name":"Enzyme","weight":0.797676,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Enzyme"},{"name":"Enzyme inhibitor","weight":0.758091,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Enzyme_inhibitor"},{"name":"Blood","weight":0.756683,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood"},{"name":"Drug","weight":0.734391,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug"},{"name":"Blood pressure","weight":0.72365,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood_pressure"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.701843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Artery","weight":0.551693,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Artery"},{"name":"Cardiology","weight":0.542846,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cardiology"},{"name":"Angioten